keyrad is a Go-based RADIUS server that authenticates users against Keycloak,
supporting password and OTP (TOTP) flows with challenge-response.

This plugin adds an OPNsense web GUI under Services > keyrad RADIUS to manage
the keyrad daemon:

  * Keycloak connection settings (token/admin API URL, realm, client id/secret,
    TLS verification)
  * RADIUS listener address/port and authentication options (PAP,
    challenge-response, Message-Authenticator, OTP challenge message)
  * FreeRADIUS-style RADIUS clients (clients.conf) with shared secrets
  * Scope/role/group to RADIUS attribute mappings, including Vendor-Specific
    Attributes (VSA) and regular-expression scope keys
  * Service control (start/stop/restart/status) and configuration apply

The keyrad daemon binary itself is expected at /usr/local/bin/keyrad. Build it
for FreeBSD from https://github.com/gpappsoft/keyrad (GOOS=freebsd) and install
it before enabling the service.
